# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend environment (Vite)
#
# The backend has its own separate config - see the root .env.example.
# Do NOT copy backend variables here.
#
# SECURITY: Vite inlines every VITE_-prefixed variable into the public
# JS bundle at BUILD time. Anything here is readable by any visitor via
# devtools. Never put a secret, API key, or database URL in this file.
# Backend secrets belong in server/.env and never leave the server.
#
# These are compile-time constants, not runtime config: changing one
# requires a rebuild, not just a restart.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# Base URL of the API, WITHOUT a trailing /api - the client appends it.
#
# Leave this BLANK for:
#   - local development (Vite proxies /api to localhost:5000)
#   - production on Render (the API serves this build from the same origin)
#
# Set it ONLY when the frontend is hosted on a different domain than the
# API (e.g. Vercel + Render). That is a cross-site setup, which also
# requires COOKIE_SAMESITE=none on the server or the browser will drop
# the auth cookie.
#
# Example: VITE_API_URL=https://email-automation-web.onrender.com
VITE_API_URL=
